original B2 false-green: a hash passes bit-identical garbage). Leave DISARMED if not
fully green.

ROOT CAUSE (the real soup, beyond the two diagnosed lifecycle bugs)
-------------------------------------------------------------------
The prior B2 "ring = soup" was the FLOAT ring attention kernel (k_attn_decode_ring,
acc += q[i]*k[i]) losing S1's build-determinism on the 40/48 SWA layers. S1 made
BYTE-EXACT integer decode the DEFAULT chat path precisely because FP-codegen reorders
near-tied logits across rebuilds, flipping a thin rank-2 margin coherent<->garbage.
But in g4_kv_step the ring branch took PRECEDENCE over the byte-exact (bx_on) branch,
so arming the ring silently dropped 40/48 layers back onto non-deterministic float
attention -> rank-2+ reorder -> soup. The attention MATH was correct (slot=(s0+j)%Wring
matches the proven one-shot G-P3-R2.b-2a); the bug was that the ring bypassed byte-exact.

THE FIXES (engine-only; null floor untouched)
---------------------------------------------
1. NEW k_attn_decode_ring_bx (cuda_forward.cu): k_attn_decode_win_bx (exact-integer
   dual-prime dot + FB30 softmax, reduction-order-immune / build-independent) with the
   ring slot remap (s0+j)%Wring. g4_kv_step dispatches it when (ring_W>0 && !global &&
   bx_on) so the 40 SWA layers stay byte-exact when the ring is armed. (ring && !bx_on
   still uses the float ring; bx_on is the chat default per S1.)
2. Journal-overflow auto-advance (cuda_forward.cu g4_kv_step, once per step before the
   layer loop): when (dpos_host - commit_pos) >= Jmax, set commit_pos = dpos_host -
   (Jmax-1). Chat never calls gemma4_kv_commit, so commit_pos stayed 0 and g4_kv_step
   hard-failed (return -1) past ~Jmax(=64) positions -> decode died. Dropping rewind
   history older than Jmax is safe for forward chat (it never rewinds mid-turn); the
   curator/#222 rewind callers DO commit, so this never trips for them.
3. Per-request reset via gemma4_kv_reset, NOT gemma4_kv_rewind(pos) (routes.rs
   run_kvdecode_chat + new glue sp_daemon_cuda_kvdecode_reset + dispatch kv::reset).
   rewind(pos) replays the SWA-owner undo-journal in reverse and reads jK/jV[L]+j*kvd
   for j up to pos-1 -> OOB past the flat Jmax*kvd journal once pos>Jmax. reset() just
   zeroes dpos/commit_pos/jcur; stale ring slots are never read (next turn rewrites
   them in position order). Equivalent to rewind on the non-ring full-cache path.
